article.headline: Hawaii 69, Utah St. 61
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Matt Gibson scored 18 of his 20 points in the second half to lead Hawaii to a 69-61 win over Utah State on Monday night. Bobby Nash added 15 points for the Rainbow Warriors (12-9, 3-5 Western Athletic Conference) and teammate Matt Lojeski had 11. Chaz Spicer led Utah State (15-7, 4-4 WAC) with 18 points. WAC leading scorer Jaycee Carroll added 13 points for the Aggies on just 5-of-13 shooting. Trailing by as many as seven points midway through the second half, Hawaii responded with a 25-6 run, keyed by 14 points from Gibson, to go up 63-51 with 2:23 remaining. The Aggies would get no closer than eight the rest of the way. Hawaii opened the second half with a 6-0 spurt, forcing three Utah State turnovers during the stretch, to take a 31-25 lead with 17:03 remaining. But back-to-back 3-pointers by the Aggies tied the game at 31 with 16:14 to go. Utah State used a 9-2 spurt to take its biggest lead of the game, 45-38, with 10:04 remaining. The game, which featured seven ties and six lead changes, was tied 25-all at halftime.
